ironmental engineering, sociology, and urban planning examine twelve of LBJ’s key domestic accomplishments in the areas of citizenship and immigration, social and economic policy, science and technology, and public management. Their findings illustrate the enduring legacy of Johnson’s determination and skill in taking advantage of overwhelming political support in the early years of his presidency to push through an extremely ambitious and innovative legislative agenda, and emphasize the extraordinary range and extent of LBJ’s influence on American public policy and administration.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh1 aBean, Frank D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrown, Susan K., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCastillo, Esther, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChapa, Jorge, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChapman, Gary, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDallek, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFrancis, Kimberly, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFrumkin, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGlickman, Norman J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGlickman, Norman J., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLynn Jr, Laurence E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLynn, Laurence E., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aOrfield, Gary, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOsborne, Cynthia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRose, Eliza